Detailed Description

SampleList is a sorted list in ascending order for discrete function samples x=f(t) or value pairs (t,x). Multiple values x for the same t are replaced with the mean.

This list is designed for rare additions and removals only and is slow when adding items in not-ascending order. Better fill it directly in the constructor.

int MathNet.Numerics.SampleList.Locate ( double  t,
int  nearIndex 
)

Find the index i of a sample near t such that t[i] <= t <= t[i+1].

This method is faster if the expected index is near nearIndex (compared to the list size) but may be slower otherwise (worst case: factor 2 slower, best case: log2(n) faster).

Returns:
The lower bound index of the interval, -1 or Size-1 if out of bounds.
